(name 'WebClient-Core-ar.82'message 'Provides a simple url-based registry for accessing and running multiple WebServer instances. Thus, one can now run WebServer for site ''http://www.mysite.com'' via:	server := WebServer forUrl: ''http://www.mysite.com''.but then launch it as appropriate via:	server listenOn: 8080 interface: #[192 168 0 1].making it easier to distinguish the (potentially proxied and tunneled) listener end from the public visible url (which can be used when handling requests). Thus, one can now also register both http and https handlers via:	httpSite := WebServer forUrl: ''http://www.mysite.com''.	httpSite listenOn: 8080. "assuming proxied via apache"	secureSite := WebServer forUrl: ''https://secure.mysite.com''.	secureSite listenOn: 8443. "assuming proxied via stunnel"yet the handlers can access the ''correct'' server url by looking at a ''request server siteUrl'' to retrieve the proper base URL.'id '8f077c95-ed44-1c40-8652-af0c93d7a4d3'date '1 November 2010'time '9:21:29.287 pm'author 'ar'ancestors ((id '94c38969-955b-8e46-9156-c52367022733'))stepChildren ())